## Hard Fork Declaration — 2026-04-14

    Per producer decision 2026-04-14 (Option C in architecture triage
    "invasive vs isolated crate vs hard fork"), BPT-NEXT is declared a
    PERMANENT HARD FORK of instructkr/claw-code.

    Implications:
    1. BPT-NEXT will NOT pursue upstream contribution for its divergent
       features (Black Pool 5-need alignment: SVN adaptation, /sync and
       /fork commands, self-built indexing bridge, identity tracking,
       memory-writeback hooks). These features are BPT-specific and do
       not match claw-code's multi-provider CLI focus.
    2. Upstream patches MAY be cherry-picked into BPT-NEXT at producer's
       discretion, but there is NO commitment to track upstream main.
    3. Any code we add is licensed MIT to match the upstream workspace
       declaration (rust/Cargo.toml `license = "MIT"`) and remain
